As Seen In CompositesWorld






 
 Current state of the M&A and capital markets – sell, sell, SELL!! 
            
                Current market conditions suggest that 2017 should see sustained M&A activity, despite the 2016 reduction.





 
 PolyOne’s carbon fiber underbody brace used for C7 Chevrolet Corvette
            
                Advanced composite underbody braces (available as a performance upgrade for all C7 Corvettes) reportedly reduce weight and increase flexural stiffness versus aluminum.  






 
 PolyOne Advanced Composites lays groundwork for Polystrand and Gordon Composites
            
                PolyOne Advanced Composites will include Polystrand, Gordon Composites and the company's existing Glasforms product line.








 
 Southern States selects PolyOne’s GlasArmor composite panels 
            
                The products protect and camouflage utility substations and other critical facilities and equipment to mitigate physical attacks.





 The Composites Group strengthens senior management
            
                Hector Diaz-Stringel, Dwight Morgan and Marc Imbrogno join top leadership at the Highlands Heights, Ohio-based supplier of thermoset molding compounds and molded composites.




 PolyOne, Xenia to cooperate on carbon fiber composite development
            
                Thermoplastic resins specialist PolyOne and carbon fiber specialist Xenia will target metallic and thermoset composite applications for conversion to carbon fiber/thermoplastics composites use.






 Long-fiber thermoplastic compound
            
                PolyOne Corp. has launched OnForce LFT long-fiber thermoplastic compounds.




 PolyOne looks to enhance wood composite systems
            
                Fiber treatment technology is designed to enhance resistance to weathering, mold and mildew, scratching, staining and water absorption.




 Color, additive solutions for natural fiber composites
            
                PolyOne Corp. has developed a series of
solutions for natural fibers designed to expand processing and material
options for the composites market.






 Zyvex, PolyOne win grant for carbon nanotube composite development
            
                The $4.9 million grant will fund carbon nanotube development in thermoplastics.




 PolyOne, Zyvex to collaborate on carbon nanotube applications
            
                Under the agreement, the companies will provide carbon nanotube-filled polymer materials for structural and electrically conductive applications.




 News briefs -- Jan. 20, 2009
            
                High Modulus names Gary Brownrigg general manager of its Queensland, Australia operation; Spartech names Tim Hamilton director of marketing development; PolyOne launches Chinese-language version of its website.






 Archer Daniels Midland Co. & PolyOne Corporation
            
                 Archer Daniels Midland Company (ADM, Decatur, Ill. ) and PolyOne Corporation (Cleveland, Ohio) announced Sept.  22 that they will collaborate on development and commercialization of bio-based plasticizers from corns and oilseeds for use in polymer formulations. 

























Product Categories of
                        PolyOne Corp.





